      <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">OXYPHENBUTAZONE</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">1,778 points · 15 letters · Across three Triple Word squares</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The theoretical maximum single-word score in Scrabble history. While almost impossible to play in a real game, it represents the absolute ceiling of what the scoring system allows. In practice, QUIXOTRY (365 pts) holds the record for the highest verified single-turn play.</p>
